In addition to her many accomplishments, media mogul Mo Abudu has become the newest grandma in town as her daughter, Temidayo, just welcomed a bundle of joy! Breaking the good news at the weekend, she wrote: “All glory to God, I became a grandma today. My darling Temidee gave birth to a bouncing baby boy. Lord I am so, so grateful. Dear Temidayo and Adebola, the biggest congratulations. God’s love, favour and blessings now and always.” Temidayo and her spouse, Ade got married at the Westminister House Registry in Marylebone, London on June 10, 2019 after they had celebrated their traditional wedding on March 24, 2019. They then went on to hold a glamorous white wedding in California.